'''March Meeting''' is an annual gathering of international art practitioners and art institutions in [[Middle East]] and [[North Africa]]. Organized by [[Sharjah Art Foundation]] and was launched in 2008 in the city of [[Sharjah]], [[United Arab Emirates]], to encourage regional art professionals to connect, partner and share ideas in the sphere of contemporary art.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Seaman|first1=Anna|title=Sharjah’s 2015 March Meeting kick off|url=http://www.thenational.ae/arts-lifestyle/art/sharjahs-2015-march-meeting-kick-off}}</ref>
== Editions == * '''2008''': Twenty-four delegates attended the first meeting held in Sharjah, in collaboration between the [[Sharjah Biennial]], the Young Arab Theatre Fund, Start and [[Art Dubai]] * '''2009''': Held between 16–20 March in collaboration between Sharjah Biennial, [[Tate Modern]] and 25 International [[curator]]s from across the region and the UK to participate in a long week intensive workshop for young curators * '''2010''': Held in collaboration with ArteEast, The programme featured a series of public talks by different speakers, including [[Abdelfattah Kilito]] and [[Okwui Enwezor]]. the event also featured for the first time, Dardashat, an informal project discussions highlighting nearly sixty new projects from around the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=Desert Brainstorming Sharjah’s Third March Meeting|url=http://metropolism.com/reviews/desert-brainstorming/}}</ref> * '''2011:''' The fourth annual March Meeting featured 42 institutions representative, artists and art professionals in the Middle East, North Africa and South Asia. took place in [[Sharjah]] from March 13 to March 15, 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|title = UAE: 4th Annual March Meeting {{!}} e-flux|url = http://www.e-flux.com/announcements/uae-4th-annual-march-meeting/|website = www.e-flux.com|accessdate = 2015-09-09}}</ref> * '''2012:''' Held between 17–19 of march with more than 80 speakers participated including: Yuko Hasegawa, Eungie Joo, [[Hans-Ulrich Obrist|Hans Ulrich Obrist]], Susanne Pfeffer, [[Beatrix Ruf]] many others. * '''2013:''' Took place from March 14 to 17, during the opening week of [[Sharjah Biennial]] 11. list of speakers included [[Sarat Maharaj]],Paulo Herkenhoff, [[Hu Fang]] and others. * '''2014:''' Curated by Eungie Joo, the forthcoming 2015 Sharjah Biennial 12, included Kristine Khouri, Rasha Salti, Eric Baudelaire, Ayreen Anastas, Rene Gabr, [[Christine Tohmé|Christine Tohme]], Tarek Abu El Fetouh, Sarah Rifky and others.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Come Together|url = http://www.ibraaz.org/reviews/62|website = Ibraaz|accessdate = 2015-09-09}}</ref> * '''2015:''' Held between 11 and 16 May as part of an extended conversation that began with March Meeting 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Concept of state reassessed at Sharjah Biennial - Stage & Street - Arts & Culture - Ahram Online|url = http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/5/35/130871/Arts--Culture/Stage--Street/Concept-of-state-reassessed-at-Sharjah-Biennial.aspx|website = english.ahram.org.eg|accessdate = 2015-09-09}}</ref>
